<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6249&amp;p=59479#p59479</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6249&amp;p=59479#p59479"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Anti Cheat system?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6249&amp;p=59479#p59479"><![CDATA[
It's pretty simple, you just use it like normal memory - except that you don't normally clear it when the cart is reset.  You put a signature byte/word in SRAM (like $55AA) when you first initialize it.  Then on later resets, you don't initialize it if the signature is there.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Thu Apr 01, 2010 4:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
