<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6249&amp;p=59470#p59470"><![CDATA[
Your mechanism can only work against emulators with buggy save states. A correct one cannot be detected because it restores everything perfectly. Imagine that the universe had a save state made, and then run forward a year, and then the state restored just now. Would you be able to tell?<br /><br />Your best approach is to put emulator detection and refuse to run unless it's an actual NES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Thu Apr 01, 2010 3:06 pm</p><hr />
